Casinatem] Varro’s estate, ⁴ fundus,⁷ at Casinum, now San Germano, was on the Via Latina, seven miles from Aquinum. Cicero says ⁴ Casinas‚’ Abrami remarks, be- cause Varro had also a villa at Tusculum. This Varro is the learned M. Terentius Varro, who once commanded two legions for Pompeius in Spain (Rc. 49); but he submitted to Caesar. His reputation was that of a writer and a learned man, the most learned of the Romans. He speaks of his Casinas in his work De Re Rustica, iii. c. 5, where he had an ⁴ ornithon,’ or place for singing birds and other kinds. It was under the Mons Casinus, Monte Casino, that Varro’s Casinas was situated.
